 honors extraordinary undergraduate students for exceptional tangible intellectual achievements among them cisac honors student anand habib a senior majoring in biology with honors in international security studies he is completing an honors thesis focusing on health governance habib sees his work as an intentional synthesis of scholarship and larger social commitments he has lived this out in many ways at stanford including working on behalf of politically and medically disenfranchised people in india mexico and guatemala on campus he has turned the stanford tradition of the annual dance marathon into a vehicle dedicated to addressing the hiv aids pandemic by engaging not only stanford students but also local communities and corporations raising more than $100000 his exceptional work was recognized by his participation in the clinton global initiative university conference in april english associate professor michele elam described habib as a superb critical thinker whose work is characterized by creative genius and mature insights she holds him up as a model for others saying that he exemplifies exactly the kind of deeply informed pragmatic and caring leadership that the world needs and stanford enables html+ read more ten undergraduates receive deans award for academic accomplishment http news stanford edu news 2011 search cisac news everything news of interest oped former stanford honors student calls north korea's new leader a corleone sheena chestnut greitens the new york times on march 4 2012 cisac honors graduate wins george j mitchell scholarship november 18 2011 cisac fsi stanford announcement honors student investigates attitudes towards prenatal care in guatemala july 16 2010 in the news cisac recognizes 10 honors program graduates 2 award winners july 20 2005 press release cisac fellow wins political science dissertation award november 3 2004 news cisac recognizes 10 honors program graduates 4 with award winning theses june 15 2004 news support map & di